===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A device to hold something upright or [[aloft]].
#: ''He set the music upon the stand and began to play.''
# The platform on which a witness [[testifies]] in [[court]]; the [[witness stand]] or [[witness box]].
#: ''She took the stand and quietly answered questions.''
# A [[position]]; firm opinion; action for a purpose.
#: ''They took a firm stand against copyright infringement.''
# A particular [[grove]] or other group of [[tree]]s.
#: ''This stand of pines is older than the one next to it.''
# A contiguous group of trees sufficiently uniform in age-class distribution, composition, and structure, and growing on a site of sufficiently uniform quality, to be a distinguishable unit.
# A small building or booth, as in a [[bandstand]] or [[hamburger stand]].
# A designated spot where someone or something may stand or wait: ''[[taxi stand]]''.
# {{cricket}} A [[partnership]].

